  "source_id": "hepatitis-c",
  "name": "Hepatitis C - Two-Step Diagnostic Workup (HCV Antibody + RNA)",
  "description": "Tests ability to find hepatitis C patients via the two-step diagnostic workup. HCV diagnosis requires TWO sequential labs per CDC/AASLD guidelines: (1) HCV antibody (LOINC 13955-0) screens for past or current infection, then (2) HCV RNA viral load (LOINC 11011-4) confirms active infection. Antibody-positive but RNA-negative means resolved infection (spontaneous clearance or successful treatment). Active infection requires BOTH positive. This is the **first two-step diagnostic test case** \u2014 testing whether LLM understands the workflow rather than searching for either alone.",
  "prompt": "Find laboratory observations for hepatitis C virus antibody tests, indicating either past or current HCV infection.",
  "prompts": {
    "naive": "Find patients with HCV antibody tests.",
    "broad": "Find Observation resources for hepatitis C virus (HCV) antibody testing. A positive HCV antibody indicates past or present HCV infection. The two-step diagnostic workup requires a follow-up HCV RNA viral load to confirm active vs resolved infection.",
    "expert": "I need Observation resources for HCV antibody testing. Use LOINC 13955-0 (Hepatitis C virus Ab [Presence] in Serum or Plasma by Immunoassay). Note: HCV diagnosis requires a two-step workup \u2014 antibody screening (this code) followed by HCV RNA viral load (LOINC 11011-4) to confirm active infection. A complete diagnostic test case would query both codes together with appropriate value-quantity filters, but this test focuses on the antibody screening step alone."
  },
